> ## Chimaera  <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?1;15;156;7;15;22;36;66;0;26;0;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;1;;3;;;;;;;;;;1;;;;;;;;10;;;;;; -->
>*Large monstrosity, chaotic neutral*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 15 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 152 (16d10 + 64)
> - **Speed** 30 ft., fly 60 ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|19 (+4)|12 (+1)|18 (+4)|7 (-2)|12 (+1)|11 (+0)|
>___
> - **Senses** darkvision 60ft., passive Perception 11
> - **Languages** -
> - **Challenge** 7 (2,900 XP)
> ___
> ***Two Heads.*** The chimaera has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks and on saving throws against being blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, stunned, and knocked unconscious.
>
> ***Wakeful.*** While the chimaera sleeps, one of its heads is awake.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The chimaera makes two bite attacks, one of which can be replaced with one breath weapon attack.
> 
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target.
*Hit:* 13 (2d8 + 4) piercing damage plus  3 (1d6) damage of same type as one of the chosen breath weapons.
>
> ***Breath Weapons.*** Choose two breath weapons from the "Chimaera Breath Weapon" sidebar.
>


\columnbreak

> ##### Chimaera Breath Weapon
> <br>    ***Poison Spit (Recharge 6).*** *Ranged Weapon Attack:* +7 to hit, reach 30/45 ft., one creature. Hit: 22 (5d8) poison damage. Hit or miss, the poison then splashes around. The target and each creature within 5 feet of it must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or take 18 (4d8) poison damage.
> <br>    In addition, each creature hit by the poison must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw, or be poisoned until the end of the chimera's next turn.
>
> ***Lightning Breath (Recharge 6).*** The chimaera exhales a bolt of lighting at a creature within 30 feet of it. That creature must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 22 (5d8) lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a success. Afterwards, the bolt jumps to a second creature within 30 feet of the first target and then to a third creature within 30 feet of the second one. 
>
> ***Acid Breath (Recharge 6).*** The chimaera ejects acid in a 20-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC l5 Dexterity saving throw, taking 18 (4d8) acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.
> <br>    Further more, any nonmagical armor made of metal that is hit by the acid corrodes. After receiving damage, the armor takes a permanent and cumulative -1 penalty to armor class. If its penalty drops to -5, the armor is destroyed.
>
> ***Ice Jet (Recharge 6).*** The chimaera exhales a frigid beam of blue-white light forming a line 80 feet long and 5 feet wide in any direction it wants.  Each creature in the line must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 13 (3d8) cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one and it becomes incapacitated until the start of the chimaera's next turn.
>
> ***Fire Breath (Recharge 6).*** The chimaera exhales fire in a 45-foot cone. Each creature in that area must succeed against a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or take 11 (2d10) fire damage and catch fire; until someone takes an action to douse the fire, the creature takes 5 (1d10) fire damage at the start of each of its turns.




\pagebreakNum



