> ## Faerie Dragon <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?1;13;130;6;13;32;0;32;0;32;0;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;1;;3;;;;;;;;;;1;1;;;;;;;10;;;;;; -->
>*Medium fey, unaligned*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 13
> - **Hit Points** 130 (20d8 + 40)
> - **Speed** 10 ft., fly 40 ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|11 (+0)|16 (+3)|14 (+2)|7 (-2)|12 (+1)|10 (+1)|
>___
> - **Skills** Perception +4, Stealth +6
> - **Senses** passive Perception 14
> - **Languages** -
> - **Challenge** 5 (1,800 XP)
> ___
> ***Magic Resistance.*** The faerie dragon has advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The faerie dragon makes two bite attacks.
> 
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 16 (3d8 + 3) piercing damage.
>
> ***Mana Flare (1/day).*** The faerie dragon channels magical energies that damage foes when they cast spells near it. Until the end of it's next turn, whenever an enemy within 30 ft from the faerie dragon casts a spell, that creature needs to succeed a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw or take 3 (1d6) points of damage per level of the spell it cast.
> <br>    In addition, if the dragon succeeds on a saving throw against an enemies spell, mana flare automatically recharges.
>
> ### Reactions
> 
> ***Phase Shift (Recharge 5-6).*** Whenever the fairie dragon takes damage, it can use its reaction to immediately become incorporeal until its next turn. While incorporeal, it cannot attack, move or take any actions and it remains visible as a ghostly outline.

<br>

> ##### Variant: Tiny Fearie Dragons <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?0;13;22;5;13;8;0;8;0;8;0;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;1;;3;;;;;;;;;;1;1;;;;;;;10;;;;;; -->
>
> Many faerie dragons are naturally very small in size and usually harmless if encountered alone, while quite dangerous if someone face them in groups.
>
> A tiny faerie dragon has the same statistics as a faerie dragon, except it has 22 (5d4+10) hit points, it has CR 1 and it does not have the *multiattack* and *mana flare*. In addition, it has Perception +3, Stealth +5 and its bite attack is +5 to hit and deals 8 (2d4 + 3) piercing damage. 

