> ## Two-legged Hydra <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?1;15;180;8;15;54;0;51;0;51;0;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;;;3;;;;;;;;;;1;;;;;;;;10;;;;;; -->
>*Large monstrosity, unaligned*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 15 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 180 (19d10 + 76)
> - **Speed** 30 ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|20 (+5)|12 (+1)|18 (+4)|4 (-3)|10 (+0)|7 (-2)|
>___
> - **Skills** Perception +3
> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 13
> - **Languages** -
> - **Challenge** 8 (3,900 XP)
> ___
> ***Multiple Heads.*** The hydra has three heads. While it has more than one head, the hydra has advantage on saving throws against being blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, stunned, and knocked unconscious.
>
> ***Reactive Heads.*** For each head the hydra has beyond one, it gets an extra reaction that can be used only for opportunity attacks.
>
> ***Wakeful.*** While the hydra sleeps, at least one of its heads is awake.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The hydra makes as many bite attacks as it has heads.
> 
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +8 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target.
*Hit:* 12 (2d6 + 5) piercing damage plus 5 (2d4) poison damage.
>
> ***Venom Spit (Recharge 5-6).*** *Ranged Weapon Attack:* +8 to hit, reach 30/45 ft., one creature. Hit: 54 (12d8) poison damage. In addition, the target must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution  saving throw, or be poisoned until the end of the hydra's next turn.

<br> 

> ##### Variant: Gahz'rilla Spawn
>
> The children of the mighty Gahz'rilla inherit its power over ice and use it against their foes, instead of venom. 
>
> The Gahz'rilla spawn has the same statistics as a hydra, except that its bite attack deals cold damage instead of poison and in place of the venom spit action it has the following:
>
> ***Arctic Beam (Recharge 5-6).*** *Ranged Weapon Attack:* +8 to hit, reach 30/45 ft., one creature. Hit: 44 (8d10) cold damage. In addition, the target must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity  saving throw, or become restrained. 
> 
> At the beginning of each of its turns, it may make a DC 15 Strength saving throw to end the effect on a success.


