> ## Four-legged Hydra <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?1;15;147;7;14;48;0;39;0;39;0;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;;;3;;;;;;;;;;1;;;;;;;;10;;;;;; -->
>*Huge monstrosity, unaligned*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 15 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 147 (14d12 + 56)
> - **Speed** 30 ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|19 (+4)|12 (+1)|18 (+4)|4 (-3)|10 (+0)|7 (-2)|
>___
> - **Skills** Perception +3
> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 13
> - **Languages** -
> - **Challenge** 6 (2,300 XP)
> ___
> ***Multiple Heads.*** The hydra has three heads. While it has more than one head, the hydra has advantage on saving throws against being blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, stunned, and knocked unconscious.
>
> ***Reactive Heads.*** For each head the hydra has beyond one, it gets an extra reaction that can be used only for opportunity attacks.
>
> ***Vile Blood.*** Whenever the hydra takes piercing or slashing damage, its blood sprays the attacker, dealing 7 (2d6) poison damage.
>
> ***Wakeful.*** While the hydra sleeps, at least one of its heads is awake.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The hydra makes as many bite attacks as it has heads.
> 
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target.
*Hit:* 13 (2d8 + 4) piercing damage.
>
> ***Breath Weapon.*** Choose the breath weapon from the "Hydra Breath Weapon" sidebar.

\columnbreak

> ##### Hydra Breath Weapon
> <br>     ***Rolling Bile (Recharge 5-6).*** The hydra spews a ball of putrid bile at a point within 20 feet from it. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius sphere centered on that point must make a DC 14 Dexterity saving throw taking 21 (6d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.
> <br>    ***Crackling Thunder (Recharge 5-6).*** The hydra spews bolts of lighting in a 15-foot cone. Every creature must succeed against a DC 14 Dexterity saving throw or take 18 (4d8) lightning damage and it cannot use its reactions until the start of hydra's next turn.
> <br>    ***Ball of Fire (Recharge 5-6).*** The hydra spews a large ball of fire at a point within 15 feet from it. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius sphere centered on that point must make a DC 14 Dexterity saving throw taking 14 (4d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The fire spreads around corners. It lasts for 10 minute. When a creature enters the burning area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, takes 3 (1d6) fire damage.

